headline.main: Sugar and Corn Reach Secret Deal Over Sweeteners

docs.abstract: Sugar and corn industries end their billion-dollar fight over sweeteners in clandestine out-of-court settlement.
docs.lead_paragraph: The sugar and corn industries ended their billion-dollar battle over sweeteners on Friday in a secret out-of-court settlement.

headline.main: Urban Students Grow Food at Los Angeles School Garden

headline.print_headline: Sugar, Corn Industries Settle Sweetener Spat; Terms Secret
headline.main: Sugar, Corn Industries Settle Sweetener Spat; Terms Secret

docs.lead_paragraph: A bitter billion-dollar battle in the sweetener wars came to an end Friday as sugar processors and the makers of high fructose corn syrup announced a secret out-of-court settlement.
docs.snippet: A bitter billion-dollar battle in the sweetener wars came to an end Friday as sugar processors and the makers of high fructose corn syrup announced a secret out-of-court settlement.

headline.print_headline: Venture Firm Andreessen Horowitz Launches $200 Million Bio Fund
headline.main: Venture Firm Andreessen Horowitz Launches $200 Million Bio Fund

docs.lead_paragraph: Venture firm Andreessen Horowitz put itself on the map with software investing. Now, it plans to take its software-heavy approach to biology and medicine, with a new $200 million fund for the hybrid sector and a former Stanford professor to run it.

headline.print_headline: San Francisco Students Battle Campus Sugary Drink Contract
headline.main: San Francisco Students Battle Campus Sugary Drink Contract

docs.lead_paragraph: Students at a San Francisco university are objecting to plans to give "pouring rights" to Coca -Cola, Pepsi or another sugary drink company.
